Tucson draws Talon closser to him in a tender embrace, and returns her kiss 
as she had returned his.  He decided that true courtship was best kept for 
when he could finally see her as he hoped to see her, with his own eyes. 
Yet, at this moment he was very happy.  Just to have someone in his life was 
a gift enough for him.

&quot; When I first came back online, I thought there may have been a power 
outage in the med bay.  Then I was told it was no loss of power.  The medics 
told me that the cranial shot I sustained was the culprit for my visual 
impairment and that they weren&#39;t positive, but thought the damgage could be 
reversed.  After that, I recovered from other physical damages, but got used 
to being blind.  Other senses compensated for that and I just accepted it 
for what it was.  Then an Autobot engineer came up with the idea of fitting 
me with a sonar system, and it worked.  I suppose I won&#39;t be needing it 
anymore once the repairs are complete.  That&#39;s - if it can be repaired.&quot;

He sighs.

&quot; I knew it would take a long time, so I procrastinated and things got out 
of hand during the wars against the predicons and Decepticons, so I put that 
on hold for a while, until we found a moment of calm.  So much for that. 
Now that Hydras and the Decepticons are at full force, and us with just a 
small handful of warriors, I fear that a full sense of calm won&#39;t be 
achieved.  It&#39;s up to Rodimus, Lord Elder and myself to get us to that 
point.  I know we can do it, and if I&#39;m going to pull my weight in this war, 
I have to have all my senses online, including my sight.&quot;

His crystal blue optics although dimmed, shimmer like aquamarines against 
the sun, as the light of the room catches them. Only until his sight is 
returned, would they once again be iluminated with the same light as the 
optics of all the others.



